@startuml
' @id(DOM-FONT-DATABASE)
' @id(DOM-OCL-VIEW)
' @desc(DOM-FONT-DATABASE, "The font database the SVG rasterizer depends on; populated once with system fonts before the first parse/render.")
' @desc(DOM-OCL-VIEW, "Viewer state for a selected .ocl constraint file: sub_mode (Source = raw OCL text, Diagram = synthesized constraints SVG) and the loaded diagram page.")
' Objective-side viewer domain: the font database the SVG rasterizer
' depends on, plus the OCL-view state added this cycle.
title Viewer domain — font database + OCL view (objective)

enum OclSubMode {
  Source
  Diagram
}

class SvgRasterizer {
  + parse(bytes) : Tree
  + render(tree, scale) : Pixmap
}

class FontDatabase {
  + fontCount : int
  + defaultFamily : String
  + loadSystemFonts() : void
}

class OclView {
  + subMode : OclSubMode
  + sourceText : String
  + page : Option<DiagramPage>
  + renderedSvg(oclPath) : Path
}

SvgRasterizer "1" o-- "1" FontDatabase : resolves <text> via >
OclView --> OclSubMode

note bottom of FontDatabase
  Populated once with the host's system fonts
  before the first parse/render. Constrained by
  OCL-FONTDB-POPULATED.
end note

note bottom of OclView
  Source paints sourceText (read-only); Diagram
  paints the synthesized constraints SVG on the
  shared canvas. subMode is exactly one of
  {Source, Diagram}; Diagram requires the
  rendered SVG to exist, else a placeholder
  (OCL-OCL-VIEW-SUBMODE, OCL-OCL-DIAGRAM-NEEDS-RENDER).
end note
@enduml
